-- 1. ISDIN Fusion Water Magic SPF50 (untinted)
update public.products set description = $desc$
<h3>Is ISDIN Fusion Water Magic SPF50 right for you?</h3>
<ul>
<li><strong>Anyone who dislikes the feel of sunscreen</strong> — The water-light texture is so invisible and weightless that patients who have never worn SPF daily become consistent wearers within a week.</li>
<li><strong>Oily and combination skin</strong> — The oil-free formula absorbs instantly with zero residue, leaving skin matte and comfortable from morning to evening.</li>
<li><strong>Post-treatment patients needing daily SPF</strong> — Lightweight enough to layer after Botox, fillers, Dermapen or peels without any heaviness or irritation on freshly treated skin.</li>
<li><strong>Active patients and outdoor enthusiasts</strong> — Can be applied directly onto wet skin — after swimming, sweating or water activities — making reapplication practical for the first time.</li>
<li><strong>All skin tones in the South African climate</strong> — Leaves absolutely no white cast and no greasiness even in peak Durban summer heat and humidity.</li>
</ul>

<h3>How ISDIN Fusion Water Magic SPF50 works — the science</h3>
<p>ISDIN's proprietary <strong>Fusion Water technology</strong> encapsulates SPF50 broad-spectrum UVA and UVB filters in an ultra-fine aqueous suspension that behaves like water on contact with skin — the micro-droplets burst instantly and deposit a uniform, invisible protective film without any oil phase to create drag, heaviness or pore congestion. The <strong>photostable filter system</strong> maintains full SPF50 efficacy from application through to reapplication, resisting degradation from UV exposure and perspiration. A built-in <strong>antioxidant complex</strong> neutralises the free radicals generated by UV and environmental exposure that topical SPF filters alone cannot intercept, addressing the full oxidative pathway of photoageing in a single product.</p>

<h3>What you will notice — and when</h3>
<p><strong>Immediately:</strong> Applies like water, disappears in seconds. Skin feels exactly like itself — clean, comfortable and completely uncoated. No white cast, no stickiness, no scent.<br><strong>Week 1–2:</strong> You stop noticing you are wearing SPF. The product removes every sensory barrier to daily compliance — patients who have avoided sunscreen for years wear this without hesitation.<br><strong>Month 1+:</strong> Consistent daily broad-spectrum protection prevents the incremental UV damage that accumulates into fine lines, pigmentation and uneven texture. Treatment results last measurably longer when protected every day.</p>

<h3>How to use ISDIN Fusion Water Magic SPF50</h3>
<ol>
<li>Apply as the final step of your morning skincare routine, after serum and any treatment products.</li>
<li>Dispense a generous amount and smooth evenly across face, neck and décolletage — do not under-apply as this reduces the SPF level.</li>
<li>Makeup can be applied immediately — the instant-dry formula creates a smooth, receptive base.</li>
<li>Reapply every 2 hours during sun exposure. Uniquely, this formula can be applied directly onto wet skin after swimming or exercise — no need to dry off first.</li>
</ol>

<h3>Key ingredients &amp; what they do</h3>
<table>
<tr><th>Ingredient</th><th>What it does for you</th></tr>
<tr><td>Fusion Water Technology</td><td>ISDIN's proprietary delivery system — encapsulates UV filters in an ultra-fine aqueous suspension that absorbs like water, leaving no oily residue or white cast on any skin tone.</td></tr>
<tr><td>UVA/UVB Broad-Spectrum Filters</td><td>Photostable chemical filters provide SPF50 protection against both burning UVB rays and the deeper, ageing UVA rays that penetrate cloud cover and glass.</td></tr>
<tr><td>Antioxidant Complex</td><td>Neutralises UV-generated free radicals that escape the filter barrier, preventing the oxidative cascade that drives photoageing and pigmentation independently of UV.</td></tr>
<tr><td>Oil-Free Aqueous Base</td><td>Non-comedogenic, hypoallergenic, biodegradable vehicle that delivers actives without any pore-clogging oil phase — safe for even the most acne-prone skin.</td></tr>
<tr><td>Water-Resistant Film Formers</td><td>Allow the formula to be applied on wet skin and maintain protection during water activities — a practical advantage no standard sunscreen lotion can match.</td></tr>
</table>

<h3>Dr. Bangalee's clinical perspective</h3>
<table>
<tr><td><strong>Dr. Bangalee Recommends</strong></td><td>"The Fusion Water Magic is the sunscreen I recommend for patients who have been resistant to daily SPF because of texture. Nothing else I have found comes close to its feel — it genuinely disappears on contact. For my post-treatment patients who need to protect their investment, the fact that it can be applied on wet skin also makes reapplication realistic for active patients in our climate." — Dr. Rajeev Bangalee, MB BS</td></tr>
</table>

<h3>What our patients say</h3>
<table>
<tr>
<td>"I have never worn sunscreen consistently in my life. This is the first one that actually feels like nothing. I apply it every morning now without even thinking about it." — Jason, 38</td>
<td>"After my Dermapen treatments Dr. Bangalee insisted on daily SPF. The Fusion Water is so light I forget I have it on. My skin has healed beautifully." — Naledi, 34</td>
<td>"I surf most mornings and reapplying sunscreen was always a hassle. Being able to apply this on wet skin has completely changed my routine." — Brett, 29</td>
</tr>
</table>

<h3>Frequently asked questions</h3>
<table>
<tr><td><strong>Can I really apply this on wet skin?</strong></td><td>Yes — this is one of ISDIN Fusion Water Magic's most distinctive features. The aqueous formula bonds to skin even in the presence of water, making it the most practical reapplication option for swimmers, surfers and anyone who sweats heavily.</td></tr>
<tr><td><strong>Does it leave a white cast?</strong></td><td>No — the formula contains no mineral filters (zinc oxide or titanium dioxide), so it is completely transparent on all skin tones including the deepest complexions. If you want tinted coverage, choose the Light, Medium or Bronze variants.</td></tr>
<tr><td><strong>Is it suitable for acne-prone skin?</strong></td><td>Yes — the oil-free, non-comedogenic, hypoallergenic formula has been specifically tested for acne-prone and sensitive skin. It is one of the safest daily SPF options for patients with active breakouts.</td></tr>
<tr><td><strong>Can I use it after a skin treatment?</strong></td><td>Yes — its lightweight, oil-free formula makes it an excellent post-procedure SPF. For very reactive skin immediately after Dermapen or chemical peels, Dr. Bangalee may recommend a 100% mineral option for the first 48–72 hours, after which the Fusion Water can be used.</td></tr>
<tr><td><strong>How does this compare to the tinted variants?</strong></td><td>The untinted Fusion Water Magic is completely clear — ideal for patients who already wear foundation or who prefer a no-makeup look. The Light, Medium and Bronze variants add a skin-tone-matching tint that provides light coverage and can replace foundation on its own.</td></tr>
</table>
