-- 5. ISDIN UV Mineral Brush SPF50+
update public.products set description = $desc$
<h3>Is ISDIN UV Mineral Brush SPF50+ right for you?</h3>
<ul>
<li><strong>Anyone who wears makeup and has never found a practical way to reapply SPF</strong> — The UV Mineral Brush solves the single biggest compliance problem in sun protection: how to reapply over makeup without removing everything and starting again.</li>
<li><strong>Post-pigmentation treatment patients</strong> — Consistent midday reapplication is the difference between treatment results that hold and results that fade. The Brush makes twice-daily SPF application achievable for the first time.</li>
<li><strong>Office workers and commuters with outdoor exposure</strong> — Morning SPF degrades within 2 hours of direct sun exposure. The Brush in your bag or desk drawer means no sun protection gap during a lunchtime walk or outdoor commute.</li>
<li><strong>Sensitive skin patients including rosacea</strong> — The 100% mineral formula (zinc oxide + titanium dioxide) has zero sensitising potential — safe for the most reactive skin conditions even with multiple daily applications.</li>
<li><strong>Travellers and active patients</strong> — The twist-up brush design is mess-free, compact and TSA-compliant. The most portable SPF reapplication solution available.</li>
</ul>

<h3>How ISDIN UV Mineral Brush SPF50+ works — the science</h3>
<p>The UV Mineral Brush encapsulates <strong>100% mineral SPF filters — zinc oxide and titanium dioxide</strong> — in a ultra-fine pressed powder matrix suspended in the brush head. When applied over makeup, the powder <strong>deposits a fresh mineral filter layer</strong> directly onto the skin surface without disturbing the cosmetic products underneath — rebuilding the protective barrier that morning SPF loses to UV degradation, perspiration and environmental contact throughout the day. The <strong>mineral-only formula</strong> is inherently photostable and does not require chemical conversion of UV energy to heat — meaning it maintains full SPF50+ protection from application to the next reapplication without any degradation of the active layer. The <strong>universal shade powder base</strong> has a light mattifying effect that absorbs midday sebum and refreshes the complexion simultaneously.</p>

<h3>What you will notice — and when</h3>
<p><strong>Immediately:</strong> Apply over full makeup in 10 seconds. Skin looks freshened and mattified — not powdery, not heavy, not disrupted. SPF protection is fully restored.<br><strong>Daily use:</strong> Reapplying SPF midday stops being a theoretical obligation and becomes a 10-second routine you actually do. The Brush removes every practical barrier to adequate reapplication.<br><strong>Month 1+:</strong> Patients who genuinely achieve twice-daily SPF reapplication show measurably better outcomes from pigmentation and anti-ageing treatments — the cumulative UV that slips through a morning-only SPF routine is eliminated.</p>

<h3>How to use ISDIN UV Mineral Brush SPF50+</h3>
<ol>
<li>Apply morning liquid SPF as normal — the UV Mineral Brush is your reapplication tool, not your primary morning protection.</li>
<li>Twist the base to advance powder into the brush head. Tap gently to load the bristles.</li>
<li>Sweep generously and evenly across the full face — nose, forehead, cheekbones and chin receive the most UV exposure and need full coverage. Do not just dust lightly — apply with intent.</li>
<li>Reapply every 2 hours during sun exposure, or after any extended outdoor activity. One cartridge provides approximately 3 months of daily midday reapplication.</li>
</ol>

<h3>Key ingredients &amp; what they do</h3>
<table>
<tr><th>Ingredient</th><th>What it does for you</th></tr>
<tr><td>Zinc Oxide (mineral, 100%)</td><td>Broad-spectrum mineral filter that physically reflects both UVA and UVB radiation — inherently photostable, meaning it does not degrade with sun exposure and maintains full SPF50+ throughout the application period.</td></tr>
<tr><td>Titanium Dioxide (mineral)</td><td>Enhances UVB protection in combination with zinc oxide. Both are non-nano grade — safe for sensitive skin, rosacea and reactive conditions with zero sensitising potential.</td></tr>
<tr><td>Universal Shade Powder Base</td><td>Neutral-toned powder vehicle that adapts to most skin tones, provides light mattifying and coverage refresh without adding visible powder build-up or altering the makeup underneath.</td></tr>
<tr><td>Silica Spheres</td><td>Microsphere silica particles that absorb midday sebum and soft-focus the appearance of pores and fine lines — so reapplying SPF actually improves the complexion rather than disrupting it.</td></tr>
<tr><td>Ophthalmologically Tested Formula</td><td>Specifically tested safe for use around the eye area — can be applied over the delicate periocular skin that is disproportionately sun-exposed and often missed by liquid SPF reapplication.</td></tr>
</table>

