<h3>Frequently asked questions</h3>
<table>
<tr><td><strong>Can I use this as my only morning SPF?</strong></td><td>No — the UV Mineral Brush is engineered for reapplication over an existing SPF base. Apply a full liquid SPF (such as ISDIN Fusion Water Magic SPF50) as your morning protection and use the Brush for midday and afternoon top-ups.</td></tr>
<tr><td><strong>Does the powder look cakey over makeup?</strong></td><td>No — when applied as directed (generous sweep rather than heavy build-up), the powder deposits a light, refreshing layer that mattifies and sets existing makeup rather than sitting on top of it. The silica spheres give a soft-focus rather than a powdery result.</td></tr>
<tr><td><strong>Is it suitable for sensitive skin and rosacea?</strong></td><td>Yes — the 100% mineral formula is the gentlest available SPF format. It contains no chemical filters that can trigger flushing or sensitisation in reactive conditions. Safe for daily multiple-application use on rosacea-prone skin.</td></tr>
<tr><td><strong>How does this compare to the Heliocare Compacts SPF50?</strong></td><td>Both are powder SPF reapplication tools for use over makeup. The ISDIN UV Mineral Brush uses 100% mineral filters (ideal for sensitive/reactive skin) and features a built-in brush for precise application. The Heliocare Compacts use a combination formula. Dr. Bangalee will recommend based on your skin type and treatment protocol.</td></tr>
<tr><td><strong>How long does one cartridge last?</strong></td><td>With one daily midday application to the face, a cartridge lasts approximately 3 months. If you reapply twice daily (recommended for high-sun-exposure patients and those on pigmentation protocols), budget for 6 weeks per cartridge.</td></tr>
</table>
